Definition: an essential structural component of living cells and source of energy for animals
Example: includes simple sugars with small molecules as well as macromolecular substances; are classified according to the number of monosaccharide groups they contain
Synonyms: saccharide, sugar, macromolecule, an, essential, structural, component, of, living, cells, and, source, energy, for, animals, includes, simple, sugars, with, small, molecules, as, well, macromolecular, substances, are, classified, according, to, the, number, monosaccharide, groups, they, contain
Category: noun.substance
